# LucidGate example list: exceptionfilenamelist
# Format: One filename fragment per line. It is compared with the response filename derived from URL or Content-Disposition.
# Lines beginning with # are comments and are ignored by the loader.
# To activate a rule, copy one example, remove the leading # and adapt it to your environment.
# You can include another file with: .Include<relative-or-absolute-path>
#
# Commented examples:
# setup.exe
# invoice.scr
# payload.dll
# installer.msi
# update.bat
# macro-document.docm
# passwords.zip
# secrets.tar.gz
